HEADWORD: Glunch
<hw>Glunch</hw> <pr>(gl⟦ucr⟧nch)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Glump</er>.]</ety> <def>Frowning; sulky; sullen.</def> <au>Sir W.
Scott.</au> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A sullen, angry look; a look of
disdain or dislike.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng. & Scot.]</mark></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

